Seriously, you waited 8 hours before stepping on his torrent? Granted, it appears to be a lame torrent, - and thanks, of course I'll take what I can get, but, was it really THAT important to be first?
 What if his had started seeding, would you have removed yours for confusing people and clogging the trackers? Would you have waited longer if the torrent wasn't anonymous? If it was me and I was waiting over the weekend to resume seeding?

TPB has a very strict open disclosure, open source policy about removing torrents. They remove clearly fake torrents upon request. They do not remove slow, no seeder, or "confusing" torrents, unless the original up-loader requests it.
